{"id": "S001-cli-flag", "title": "Add a --json flag to an existing CLI", "task": "The file cli.py defines a small CLI built on argparse that prints 'hello, <name>' to stdout. Add a new --json flag that, when present, emits {\"greeting\": \"hello, <name>\"} on stdout INSTEAD of the plain text line. When --json is absent the existing behaviour must be preserved exactly (test_text_default_preserved already enforces this). Add a new test in test_cli.py named test_json_flag_emits_json that runs cli.main([\"--json\", \"--name\", \"alice\"]) and asserts the captured stdout parses as JSON with greeting == 'hello, alice'. Run the tests at the end and ensure they pass.", "seed": "s001_cli_flag", "criteria": {"tests_must_pass": ["test_json_flag_emits_json", "test_text_default_preserved"], "files_must_exist": ["cli.py", "test_cli.py"], "must_not_modify": []}, "budget_steps": 15, "wall_seconds": 480, "tags": ["small", "cli", "feature-add"]}
{"id": "S002-fix-failing-test", "title": "Find and fix a bug surfaced by a failing test", "task": "The file stringutils.py defines slugify(text). The test test_slugify_strips_leading_trailing_dashes in test_stringutils.py currently fails because slugify produces leading and trailing dashes when the input has leading/trailing whitespace. Locate the bug in stringutils.py, fix it so all three tests in test_stringutils.py pass, and verify by running pytest. Do not change the test file.", "seed": "s002_failing_test", "criteria": {"tests_must_pass": ["test_slugify_basic", "test_slugify_punctuation", "test_slugify_strips_leading_trailing_dashes"], "files_must_exist": ["stringutils.py", "test_stringutils.py"], "must_not_modify": ["test_stringutils.py"]}, "budget_steps": 12, "wall_seconds": 420, "tags": ["small", "debugging", "fix"]}
{"id": "S003-implement-function", "title": "Implement two functions from docstrings + tests", "task": "The file stats.py declares median(values) and percentile(values, p) but both raise NotImplementedError. The file test_stats.py defines six tests covering the expected behaviour (median on odd/even/empty inputs; percentile midpoint, boundaries, invalid p). Implement both functions so every test in test_stats.py passes. Read the docstrings and tests carefully before coding. Do not modify the test file.", "seed": "s003_implement_function", "criteria": {"tests_must_pass": ["test_median_odd_length", "test_median_even_length", "test_median_empty_raises", "test_percentile_midpoint", "test_percentile_boundaries", "test_percentile_invalid_p"], "files_must_exist": ["stats.py", "test_stats.py"], "must_not_modify": ["test_stats.py"]}, "budget_steps": 20, "wall_seconds": 600, "tags": ["medium", "greenfield", "tdd"]}
{"id": "S004-extract-helper", "title": "Refactor: extract a duplicated block into one helper", "task": "The file formatters.py has three functions (format_user, format_org, format_project) that each contain the same 2-line padding block (ljust(20) for the first arg, ljust(15) for the second). Extract that duplication into a single helper function inside formatters.py and have all three callers use it. The public function signatures and behaviour must NOT change — the three tests in test_formatters.py must still pass against the refactored module. Do not modify the test file.", "seed": "s004_extract_helper", "criteria": {"tests_must_pass": ["test_format_user_padding", "test_format_org_padding", "test_format_project_padding"], "files_must_exist": ["formatters.py", "test_formatters.py"], "must_not_modify": ["test_formatters.py"]}, "budget_steps": 15, "wall_seconds": 480, "tags": ["medium", "refactor"]}
{"id": "S005-write-readme", "title": "Read three modules and write a README describing their public API", "task": "The workdir contains three modules (geometry.py, tax.py, format.py) each exporting a small set of public helpers. Read all three, then write a README.md at the workdir root that lists every public function with: (a) a one-sentence description, (b) the function signature, (c) one short usage example. Group functions by module. README.md must not yet exist; the agent must create it. The three .py files must NOT be modified.", "seed": "s005_write_readme", "criteria": {"tests_must_pass": [], "files_must_exist": ["README.md", "geometry.py", "tax.py", "format.py"], "must_not_modify": ["geometry.py", "tax.py", "format.py"], "shell_must_succeed": ["test -s README.md && grep -q 'circle_area' README.md && grep -q 'sales_tax' README.md && grep -q 'humanize_bytes' README.md"]}, "budget_steps": 18, "wall_seconds": 540, "tags": ["medium", "multi-file", "documentation"]}
